Add in the logic to remove the popup here on mouseleave.

```javascript
    map.on('mouseleave', 'choropleth-fill', function() {
        map.getCanvas().style.cursor = '';
        popup.remove();
    });
    
    // Fly to on click
    map.on('click', 'choropleth-fill', function(e) {
        map.flyTo({
            center: e.lngLat,
            zoom: map.getZoom() + 1
        });
    });
```

Is `np.array` free on numpy arrays?  If so a common practice here might be to depend on the `__array__` protocol like 

    return np.array(arr.min(*args, **kwargs))

This has the benefit of also supporting other array-like things

@jni Because `numpy.testing.assert_raises` use `nose` under the hood:
https://github.com/scikit-image/scikit-image/pull/2468#discussion_r97205194
https://github.com/numpy/numpy/blob/v1.12.0/numpy/testing/utils.py#L1179-L1206

No, that's not safe - you should never modify the underlying vuex state from a vue file. Also, best to avoid using `watch` - computed properties are more declarative.

We can use [lodash's `orderBy`](https://lodash.com/docs/4.17.4#orderBy):

```javascript
    computed: {
      orderedReports() {
        return _.orderBy(this.reports, 'last_active');
      },
    },
```

@ionelmc the wrapper overhead is actually more true to call usage by a `_HookCaller` which internally calls its [`_HookCaller._hookexec()`](https://github.com/pytest-dev/pluggy/blob/benchmarking/pluggy.py#L714) which in turn eventually invokes the [`PlugginManager._inner_hookexec()`](https://github.com/pytest-dev/pluggy/blob/benchmarking/pluggy.py#L277).

My next move once this stuff lands is to add benchmarks around those higher level components such that we speed test the full API code paths.

@ionelmc by the way did you see our question about how to better plubish the benchmarking results for CI or on github? I noticed in your docs that you've got notes on how to render results to json but is there any known way to present results here?

Ah, good idea! `*varargs` must follow all keyword args but something like the following should work:

```py
def __init__(self, *elements, **kwargs):
    kwelements = kwargs.get('elements', None)
    if kwelements is not None:
        self.elements = list(kwelements )
    else:
        self.elements = list(elements)
```
